<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10361495>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Key characters of the Moniligaster gravelyi Stephenson, 1915 (based on the present study). A. Ventral view of anterior region. B. Prostate of right hand side, dorsal view. C. Prostatic capsule of right hand side, slightly stretched, dorsal view. D. Spermatheca of right hand side, slightly stretched, dorsal view. Cl.—Clitellum; C.A.D.—Common atrial duct; F.P.—Female pore; M.H.L.—Mass of hairpin loops; P.C.—Prostatic capsule; P.—Prostate; P.D.—Prostatic duct; S.A.—Spermathecal ampulla; S.A.G.—Spermathecal atrial gland; S.A.G.D.—Spermathecal atrial gland duct; S.D.—Spermathecal duct; S.M.A.—Secondary male aperture; Sp.P.—Spermathecal pore; T.S.—Testis sac; Vd.—Vas deferens." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10361495/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10361497>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Current known range of Moniligaster gravelyi." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10361497/files/figure.png" ;
